    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"underfunding\" is just one way to look at it though. if you have a sudden influx of people, the sheer demand on those services goes up regardless of the budget. it seems like you're kinda dismissing the idea that mass immigration can be fundamentally destabilizing to a country's infrastructure. isn't that a real possibility that economists look at too?",
